Piwik PRO API (auto)

Download OpenAPI specification:Download

This api allows manipulating user and user group permissions for apps and meta sites.

Permission overview

Permission is a group of specific actions that user can perform on entities.

App permissions:

↓ Action \ Permission → view edit edit-publish manage
view ✔ ✔ ✔ ✔
edit ✔ ✔ ✔
publish ✔ ✔
manage ✔

Detailed description of app actions:

  • view - allows viewing an app
  • edit - allows editing an app
  • publish - allows publishing changes in Tag Manager module
  • manage - allows managing user permissions for an app
  • add - allows adding apps (owner only)
  • delete - allows deleting an app (owner only)

Meta site permissions:

↓ Action \ Permission → view edit manage
view ✔ ✔ ✔
edit ✔ ✔
view_details ✔
edit_details ✔
list_apps_in_meta_site ✔
manage ✔

Detailed description of meta site actions:

  • view - allows viewing meta site in Analytics module
  • edit - allows editing meta site reports in Analytics module
  • view_details - allows viewing meta site details in Administration module
  • edit_details - allows editing meta site details in Administration module
  • list_apps_in_meta_site - allows listing apps in a meta site
  • manage - allows managing user permissions for a meta site
  • add - allows creating new meta site (owner only)
  • delete - allows deleting meta site (owner only)
  • add_app_to_meta_site - allows adding apps to a meta site (owner only)
  • remove_app_from_meta_site - allows removing apps from a meta site (owner only)

Access Control

Entity actions

Returns granted actions to a given entity for current user.

Authorizations:
BearerAuth
path Parameters
entity_id
required
string <uuid>

UUIDv4 identifier of given entity

Responses

https://example.piwik.pro/api/access-control/v2/entry/{entity_id}

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/vnd.api+json
{
  • "data": {
    • "type": "ppms/permission/entity/actions",
    • "id": "50fca71a-e4a7-4480-a612-a9ffbdf0935f",
    • "attributes": {
      • "actions": [
        • "view",
        • "edit",
        • "publish",
        • "delete",
        • "manage",
        • "add"
        ]
      }
    }
}

Users permissions for a given app

Lists all users (but not owners) and their permissions for a given app. List contains both explicit permission of a user and implicit highest permission inherited from user groups which user belongs to.

Authorizations:
BearerAuth
path Parameters
app_id
required
string <uuid>

UUIDv4 identifier of an object

query Parameters
limit
integer [ 0 .. 1000 ]
Default: 10

Limits the number of returned items

offset
integer >= 0
Default: 0

Sets offset for list of items

search
string

Search phrase - search for e-mail or id

Responses

https://example.piwik.pro/api/access-control/v2/app/{app_id}/permission/user

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/vnd.api+json
{
  • "meta": {
    • "total": 1
    },
  • "data": [
    • {
      • "id": "985ed9d7-b652-47b8-b9cf-c17d62735261",
      • "type": "app/permission/user",
      • "attributes": {
        • "email": "example@example.com",
        • "group_permissions": {
          • "group_names": [
            • "Managers"
            ],
          • "permission": "manage"
          },
        • "permission": "manage"
        }
      }
    ]
}

path Parameters

required

UUIDv4 identifier of an object

query Parameters
limit
integer [ 0 .. 1000 ]
Default: 10

Limits the number of returned items

offset
integer >= 0
Default: 0

Sets offset for list of items

search
string

Search phrase - search for user group name and user group id

sort
string
Default: "name"
Enum: "name" "-name"

Sort field - can be reversed by adding dash before field name e.g (-name)

Apps

Apps list

Get list of apps

Full example:

/api/apps/v2?offset=100&limit=10&sort=name&search=nifty+marketing

this will list 10 apps ordered ascending by name starting on 101th matching search query "nifty marketing".

Authorizations:
BearerAuth
query Parameters
offset
integer >= 0
Default: 0

Sets offset for list of items

limit
integer [ 0 .. 1000 ]
Default: 10

Limits the number of returned items

search_query
string
Default: ""

(deprecated) Use search param instead

sort
string
Default: "-addedAt"
Enum: "name" "addedAt" "updatedAt" "-name" "-addedAt" "-updatedAt"

Sort field - can be reversed by adding dash before field name e.g (-name)

search
string
Default: ""

App search query

Responses

https://example.piwik.pro/api/apps/v2

Response samples

        • "addedAt": "2018-07-10T08:50:41+00:00",

List apps & meta sites

Get list of apps with meta sites. App with demo type will be always first on the list if exists (sorting method is irrelevant)

Full example:

/api/meta-sites/v1/apps-with-meta-sites?offset=100&limit=10&search=nifty+marketing&action=edit

this will list 10 apps and meta sites which I have access to (can execute edit action) starting on 101th matching search query "nifty marketing".

Authorizations:
BearerAuth
query Parameters
offset
integer >= 0
Default: 0

Sets offset for list of items

limit
integer [ 0 .. 1000 ]
Default: 10

Limits the number of returned items

search
string

Search phrase - search for name or id

sort
string
Default: "name"
Enum: "name" "type" "created_at" "-name" "-type" "-created_at"

Sort field - can be reversed by adding dash before field name e.g (-name)

action
string
Enum: "view" "edit"

Action to which I have access (can execute given action)

Responses

https://example.piwik.pro/api/meta-sites/v1/apps-with-meta-sites

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/vnd.api+json
{
  • "meta": {
    • "total": 2
    },
  • "data": [
    • {
      • "type": "ppms/app",
      • "id": "6edb1e3c-4c43-4760-ab76-682ad83146be",
      • "attributes": {
        • "name": "Example site",
        • "created_at": "2019-07-30T12:53:46Z"
        }
      },
    • {
      • "type": "ppms/meta-site",
      • "id": "ac62ca6b-cfd6-4161-b414-e1061baa05b7",
      • "attributes": {
        • "name": "European landing pages",
        • "created_at": "2019-02-21T02:30:12Z"
        }
      }
    ]
}

List of tags

JSON API compatibility divergence

Filters

In JSON API standard (https://jsonapi.org/recommendations/#filtering) one can request elements with multiple filter values by simply providing them separated by coma:

tags?filter[template]=piwik,adroll

This notation will not work here. You can achieve this functionality by providing multiple filters for the same parameter:

tags?filter[template][]=piwik&filter[template][]=adroll

List of variables

JSON API compatibility divergence

Filters

In JSON API standard (https://jsonapi.org/recommendations/#filtering) one can request elements with multiple filter values by simply providing them separated by coma:

variables?filter[variable_type]=url,constant

This notation will not work here. You can achieve this functionality by providing multiple filters for the same parameter:

variables?filter[variable_type][]=url&filter[variable_type][]=constant

Example: 1f74dda5-b598-41d6-a9e4-f501ef4379e1

Example: page[offset]=20

Sets offset for list of items

string [ 1 .. 255 ] characters
Example: filter[name]=Custom Javascript variable

string
Enum: "custom_javascript" "constant" "cookie" "data_layer" "dom_element" "document" "random" "url" "lookup_table"
Example: filter[variable_type]=url

Filter variable with type

filter[builtin]
boolean
Example: filter[builtin]=true

Filter variable with builtin attribute

sort
Array of strings non-empty
Items Enum: "name" "-name" "variable_type" "-variable_type" "created_at" "-created_at" "updated_at" "-updated_at"
Example: sort=name&sort=-created_at&sort=updated_at

Comma-separated sort list with given attributes: name, variable_type, created_at, updated_at

List of versions

JSON API compatibility divergence

Filters

In JSON API standard (https://jsonapi.org/recommendations/#filtering) one can request elements with multiple filter values by simply providing them separated by coma:

versions?filter[version_type][]=published,draft

This notation will not work here. You can achieve this functionality by providing multiple filters for the same parameter:

versions?filter[version_type][]=published&filter[version_type][]=draft

Queries

Execute query

API that allows querying the database directly. Please note that each request must be authenticated.

Copy definition

You can use the View API call definition option available in Analytics module in each report to get more usage examples based on your existing reports.

Compression

When requesting large amount of data, make sure to include an Accept-Encoding: gzip header to enable compression.

Cache

Please note that all query results are cached for 10 minutes.

Authorizations:
BearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
website_id
required
string <uuid>

ID of a website or a meta site.

required
Array of objects

Column definitions for the query.

date_from

List user annotations

Returns a list all user annotations available for a website. Please note that each request must be authenticated.

Authorizations:
BearerAuth
query Parameters
website_id
required
string <uuid>
Example: website_id=677fe0d3-b4f7-43ed-852d-1a9e7b8e59fb

ID of the website.

date_from
Array of strings <date> [ items <date > ]
Example: date_from=2021-05-01

Start date for the query (inclusive). You can specify mulitple dates which will be paired with corresponding date_to parameters. For example ?date_from=2020-01-01&date_to=2020-01-10&date_from=2021-06-01&date_to=2021-07-01 will create two ranges: [2020-01-01; 2020-01-10] and [2021-06-01; 2021-07-01]. Number of date_from parameters must match number of date_to parameters.

date_to
Array of strings <date> [ items <date > ]
Example: date_to=2021-05-01

End date for the query (inclusive). You can specify mulitple dates which will be paired with corresponding date_to parameters. Read more in date_from parameter description.
